1
00:00:04,600 --> 00:00:05,880
Quiet ride today, huh?

2
00:00:07,240 --> 00:00:08,800
Let's hope it's not the calm before the storm.

3
00:00:10,840 --> 00:00:13,160
What are they doing?
-One's sitting and the other's drawing.

4
00:00:13,240 --> 00:00:15,320
Go ahead.
-I’m done.

5
00:00:15,880 --> 00:00:20,200
Wow, that's beautiful, honey.
Look, Dad, how pretty she’s drawing.

6
00:00:20,280 --> 00:00:22,960
Wow, lovely.
-Lovely. You really draw beautifully.

7
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:24,840
Thanks.
-The genius girl.

8
00:00:24,920 --> 00:00:26,640
It’s not "genius," it’s "genius."

9
00:00:26,720 --> 00:00:28,720
It’s a title, like doctor.
You don’t say "doctora."

10
00:00:30,080 --> 00:00:33,720
Honey, you know what we’ll do?
When we get to Grandma's, we’ll give her the drawing as a gift,

11
00:00:33,840 --> 00:00:37,200
and then she’ll hang it on the fridge,
so everyone can see how beautifully you draw.

12
00:00:37,280 --> 00:00:40,200
Sit down, sit down, honey. Why are you promising
the girl things you can’t keep?

13
00:00:40,760 --> 00:00:43,120
What?
-My mom doesn’t like to hang drawings on the fridge.

14
00:00:43,280 --> 00:00:45,120
It messes up her decor.
-What decor?

15
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:47,840
"The aesthetics of the fridge," she calls it.

16
00:00:48,040 --> 00:00:49,280
You know how many times, as a kid,

17
00:00:49,360 --> 00:00:51,720
I brought her drawings to hang on the fridge and she...

18
00:00:52,280 --> 00:00:54,800
I want to see her not hang
her granddaughter's drawing on the fridge.

19
00:00:54,880 --> 00:00:57,320
No, really, I want to see
her say "no" to the girl.

20
00:00:57,920 --> 00:00:59,200
There goes the quiet.

21
00:01:03,080 --> 00:01:05,440
Look at me, look at me and...

22
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:17,240
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

23
00:01:17,320 --> 00:01:18,720
Oh, Shabbat Shalom.

24
00:01:18,880 --> 00:01:21,080
Shabbat Shalom, my darlings.
-Shabbat Shalom, Pinchas.

25
00:01:21,160 --> 00:01:24,200
Shabbat Shalom, Shai. How’s it going?
-As usual, everything’s fine.

26
00:01:24,320 --> 00:01:25,600
Riki in the kitchen?
-As usual.

27
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:27,360
Come on, girls, come give Grandma the drawing.

28
00:01:28,240 --> 00:01:33,800
Oh, look who’s here. Hey.
-Shabbat Shalom, Grandma.

29
00:01:33,880 --> 00:01:35,720
Shai, don’t call me Grandma, I have a name.

30
00:01:35,880 --> 00:01:38,680
Oh, sorry. Hi, Riki.
-Hi, Shai.

31
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:43,880
Tamari and Michal are on their way here and Adam...

32
00:01:43,960 --> 00:01:46,280
is bringing a new girl he says is serious this time.

33
00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:48,040
Sure.
-Sure.

34
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:49,960
Dad.
-Yes?

35
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:51,360
As a kid...

36
00:01:51,960 --> 00:01:54,560
were my drawings really that ugly?

37
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:59,160
Great, I told Mom
that one day it would come back to haunt us.

38
00:01:59,440 --> 00:02:02,440
Who’s haunting? Just asking.
-Your drawings were very pretty, Shai.

39
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:07,280
They just didn’t fit the aesthetics
of the fridge. New one. Every week a new one.

40
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:10,360
I promised myself this time
I won’t even ask what her name is.

41
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:12,840
I don’t care if it’s serious or not. Not asking.

42
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:15,720
Who are you talking about?
-About the one Adam is bringing this week.

43
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:19,280
Why should I bother?
Next week he’ll bring a new one anyway.

44
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:21,680
Why should I even bother?
-For politeness.

45
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:24,600
At my age, there’s no politeness - at my age, there’s prostate
-Okay.

46
00:02:25,760 --> 00:02:26,760
Look what we brought you.

47
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:29,040
Yes
a drawing.
Here.

48
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:32,120
The girl drew on the way and we thought
maybe you’d hang it on the fridge.

49
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:34,640
Oh.
-What happened? Is it not pretty?

50
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:37,160
No, no, no. It’s pretty,

51
00:02:37,720 --> 00:02:43,320
and
it’s, it’s lovely. Really.

52
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:45,880
Well, then hang it.
-Where?

53
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:47,360
On the fridge.

54
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:52,160
Are you sure you want me
to hang this drawing on the fridge?

55
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:54,840
Yes, I’m sure, Riki.
-Okay.

56
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:57,960
I want everyone to see
how beautifully my granddaughter draws.

57
00:02:58,560 --> 00:03:01,400
Okay. I’m already hanging it,

58
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:08,360
so everyone can see how... it’s, it’s clear.

59
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:11,160
Excuse me?
-What?

60
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:16,400
Mom says you were a wild one before the wedding too.
-Wild, wild.

61
00:03:16,480 --> 00:03:18,040
You know Mom, she’s overdoing it.

62
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:20,400
How much?
-Forget it.

63
00:03:20,480 --> 00:03:22,320
How much?
-Shai.

64
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:24,160
Dad.
-Shh.

65
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:28,400
Shh?
-There was a redemption, everyone called her Geula.

66
00:03:28,480 --> 00:03:31,880
There was Tzipi, a sister who loved to give.
-No need...

67
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:35,560
There was Ruthie, a kibbutznik
who worked in the dairy and loved to milk.

68
00:03:35,640 --> 00:03:38,160
Enough, Dad, enough, enough. No need...
-Wait, you haven't heard about Gila yet.

69
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:39,880
But I understood.
-You haven't heard about Gila who was a flutist

70
00:03:39,960 --> 00:03:42,880
and loved her magic flute.
-No. Enough. Stop. Enough.

71
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:47,280
At least you can’t complain about Adam.
-Not complaining, just jealous.

72
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:50,040
What? What are they talking about?
-About me and the...

73
00:03:50,120 --> 00:03:52,960
his prostate.
-Lovely. Sabbath delight.

74
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:57,800
Your mom hung the drawing on the fridge like a trophy.
-Really?

75
00:03:58,720 --> 00:04:02,280
Lucky.
-The luck is all hers. All hers.

76
00:04:02,360 --> 00:04:04,640
I’m going to check
if Mom needs help with something.

77
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:09,600
What? So it turns out my mom
does hang drawings on the fridge?

78
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:13,440
Turns out.
-So what, were my drawings too ugly?

79
00:04:14,920 --> 00:04:15,760
Turns out.

80
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:21,480
Rivka, do you need something?
-I need a lot of things. So what?

81
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:25,080
Are you going to give them to me? No. Just look for a second.
-At what?

82
00:04:25,160 --> 00:04:28,040
At the fridge.
-We’re not buying a new fridge.

83
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:32,520
At the drawing on the fridge.
-Oh, that’s Shai’s little one.

84
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:35,600
Let it go.
-What do you think of the drawing?

85
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:38,920
It’s a drawing by a little girl.
In an hour, you’ll put it aside

86
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:41,080
and in a week, you’ll throw it in the trash, Riki.

87
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:43,880
What do you think of the drawing itself?

88
00:04:43,960 --> 00:04:48,200
Artistically?
-Yeah, Rembrandt, artistically.

89
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:51,040
No. Psychologically.

90
00:04:51,120 --> 00:04:53,480
What psychologically? It’s a drawing by a little girl.

91
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:56,840
Come on, doesn’t the mom in the drawing look like a monster to you?

92
00:04:57,720 --> 00:05:01,000
The mom? Rivka, let’s not get carried away.

93
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:03,120
It’s... maybe the girl didn’t mean it,

94
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:05,520
maybe we don’t understand?
-What’s there to understand?

95
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:10,920
It’s right in front of our eyes.
Drawn in panda colors on paper

96
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:13,280
on my shiny fridge.

97
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:20,720
You never know.
-Pinchas, I don’t want them to say

98
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:24,640
that the writing was on the fridge
and we did nothing.

99
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:29,800
What’s that? What do you see?
-Come on, give it to me, you annoying one.

100
00:05:29,880 --> 00:05:32,200
I don’t know, looks like a cooking show or something.
-Cooking? Then why are there

101
00:05:32,280 --> 00:05:35,680
a singer and half-naked dancers?
-I don’t know, maybe it makes the food taste better.

102
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:37,360
Shabbat Shalom.

103
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:38,800
Hey. Shabbat Shalom.
-What’s up?

104
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:42,520
Where’s Mom? Is there food? I’m starving. Mom!

105
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:46,160
Shh, what’s this? Is everyone already here?
-No, Adam hasn’t arrived.

106
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:49,480
I want to tell you something but only
when everyone is here. I’m so excited.

107
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:53,720
Why are you yelling like that? What happened? I was already worried.

108
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:56,160
Is there food? I’m starving. When are we eating?

109
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:59,760
When was the last time you came to this house and there wasn’t food?

110
00:05:59,840 --> 00:06:02,280
I just wanted to be sure. Mom, I’m hungry.

111
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:06,600
Tell me, why aren’t you making him food?
Why does he have to get to this point?

112
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:08,760
It’s not healthy.
-How did this happen to me? What did I do?

113
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:09,880
Not enough, apparently.

114
00:06:09,960 --> 00:06:11,400
Schnitzels?
-Yeah, son.

115
00:06:11,520 --> 00:06:13,600
Since when?
-Since two weeks ago.

116
00:06:13,880 --> 00:06:18,160
I found it by chance in the fridge and decided to serve it.
-Really?

117
00:06:18,240 --> 00:06:22,800
No. When was the last time
you ate a not-fresh schnitzel in this house?

118
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:25,600
Okay, why are you being annoying? I just wanted to be sure.

119
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:29,360
I’m going to get a schnitzel.
-I’ll come with you because you won’t find it.

120
00:06:30,440 --> 00:06:33,040
What’s up? Michali?
-Michali has something to tell us.

121
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:36,240
But she's waiting for Adam to come.
-You're pregnant.

122
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:40,200
I told Pinchas
that there's no way you gained that much weight.

123
00:06:40,280 --> 00:06:42,720
You must be pregnant.
-I'm not pregnant.

124
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,560
What, I gained weight?
-No, no. Not at all.

125
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:46,120
What do you mean?
-Just in your body.

126
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:51,560
But this way there's proportion, with the head.
Because you have a really big head.

127
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:53,240
I have a big head?

128
00:06:55,160 --> 00:06:57,960
Itamar, look. What do you see?
-What is it?

129
00:06:58,120 --> 00:07:00,480
It's a drawing that Shai's little one made. Look.

130
00:07:04,840 --> 00:07:08,680
I can't believe it. Since when does Mom allow
hanging drawings on the fridge?

131
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:12,240
No, not that. Look at the content of the drawing.

132
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:16,560
What do you think about the psychological stuff
hidden behind this drawing?

133
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:20,400
What, is that Shabi?
-I think so. What do you say?

134
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:22,920
The girls seem sad here. Did you notice?
-No, I didn't notice.

135
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:26,480
Shabi's teeth confused me.
-Yeah. A bit.

136
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:27,840
That's not good.

137
00:07:28,880 --> 00:07:32,400
So, this lamp is done for. Done.

138
00:07:32,960 --> 00:07:35,040
I hope you left me some schnitzels, yeah.
-Yeah, there's plenty.

139
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:36,800
Just don't finish them off. I'm starving.

140
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:40,480
I'm going back to the living room because Mom's on the attack.
Your wife is the target, by the way.

141
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:43,120
What can I do? I told her
not to look Mom in the eyes.

142
00:07:43,400 --> 00:07:45,400
It's okay, it'll toughen her up.
-Or it might kill her.

143
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:51,080
What do you think? Should I say something to him?
-I don't know what to tell you, Dad.

144
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:53,240
So don't say anything?
-See? That's exactly

145
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:54,160
why I don't encourage

146
00:07:54,280 --> 00:07:56,920
my kids to be creative.
-What, they don't draw at all?

147
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:59,800
They don't draw, don't write
and don't sculpt with Play-Doh.

148
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:02,040
I don't need them digging up stuff from their subconscious.

149
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:03,600
They should focus on practical subjects.

150
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:08,600
I do kickboxing, Pilates, and spinning.

151
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:10,800
And I go to Zumba three times a week.

152
00:08:10,920 --> 00:08:14,040
Michali, honey, it's a waste of your effort.

153
00:08:14,240 --> 00:08:17,960
It's a matter of genetics.
Your mom has a big head too.

154
00:08:18,520 --> 00:08:21,240
My mom has a big head?
-It's okay. It happens.

155
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:30,400
What are you doing?

156
00:08:30,480 --> 00:08:32,720
I want to join too.
-Aren't you too big?

157
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:35,799
You're right. I need a drawing from when I was little.

158
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:11,400
Really big head.
-My head's not big, Riki.

159
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:15,840
My head is normal for my body.
-Okay, Michali, okay. Whatever you say.

160
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:17,640
Itamar...

161
00:09:25,480 --> 00:09:28,760
So, what's up, Shabi?
-Everything's fine.

162
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:34,240
How's the little one in kindergarten?
-Actually, she's great. Really. Really.

163
00:09:34,520 --> 00:09:35,800
Yeah?
-She also loves the teacher...

164
00:09:35,880 --> 00:09:39,200
Actually, this week they did some kind of
paper mache with varnish...

165
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:41,600
Great. And how are you two, with each other?

166
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:45,120
Do you talk? Do you play together?
-Of course.

167
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:48,080
What, what do you mean? Riki, what are these questions?

168
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,920
Just, just wanted to know. It's...

169
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:56,440
Tell me, did you clean the house this week?
-Of course. What kind of question is that?

170
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:58,720
Just, just wanted to know.

171
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:03,120
Honey, do you think I have a big head?

172
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:04,760
Of course, honey.
-What?

173
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:08,680
What... you always lift the seat
in the bathroom after you go.

174
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:11,560
That's what I call a big head.
-No, not like that, honey.

175
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:14,040
Physically big.
-What, my mom...

176
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:16,120
Forget it, her sense of proportion is completely off.

177
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:19,360
You're perfectly fine for your body, honey.
-Thanks, honey.

178
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:20,600
Are you done with that?

179
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:23,080
Michal, you dabble a bit in psychology, right?

180
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:25,320
Yeah, but I can't talk
about that right now. I'm saving the message.

181
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:27,960
Later, everyone.
-Yeah, yeah, sure, but look,

182
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:30,920
What do you think about this?
-What is this drawing?

183
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:33,360
It's Shai's little one who drew it.
-No way, I'm dying.

184
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:35,480
What?
-What, it's a really disturbing drawing.

185
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:37,480
The kid looks terrified.
-No, I'm going to call Shai.

186
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:40,080
No, no, no, wait, wait, wait.
We need to handle this very gently.

187
00:10:40,320 --> 00:10:42,400
Damn, I wish I had my Barbie collection here.

188
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:43,440
That would really help me out.

189
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:46,120
She has a Barbie collection?
-Forget it, Dad. Just forget it.

190
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:47,640
Alright, I forgot.

191
00:10:47,720 --> 00:10:51,600
You don't give the girls good whacks like that?
-Of course not.

192
00:10:52,160 --> 00:10:55,480
Wait, are you telling me
you never lay a hand on them,

193
00:10:56,040 --> 00:10:59,600
a flip-flop, a rolled-up newspaper?
-What are you talking about?

194
00:11:00,280 --> 00:11:02,840
Riki, you really overdid it this time.
I don't hit my girls.

195
00:11:02,920 --> 00:11:04,840
Okay. What happened? It's not shameful.

196
00:11:04,920 --> 00:11:07,520
Kids can be really annoying at that age.

197
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:11,240
Itamar, for example, I wanted
to kill him when he was that age.

198
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:14,040
Just kill him.
-Yeah, but you didn't kill him. Right?

199
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:18,760
Right. I'm really sorry.
He still manages to annoy me.

200
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:20,640
K'
Mom `
.Batzay
Y
Mom, oh no

201
00:11:20,720 --> 00:11:24,040
The pickles,
did you make them or are they from a jar?

202
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:26,480
See? Kill him. Just kill him.

203
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:29,160
Sit down, come here for a sec.
-They're from a jar.

204
00:11:29,760 --> 00:11:30,840
Is it in vinegar or salt?

205
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:34,000
Itamar, please go get me a rolled-up newspaper.

206
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:39,520
See?
-Who is that? You and Itamar when you were little?

207
00:11:39,640 --> 00:11:41,520
Before Adam was born. But that's not important.

208
00:11:41,680 --> 00:11:43,080
Look here, on the drawing. Here, behind us.

209
00:11:43,560 --> 00:11:44,480
Wow, a drawing.

210
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:46,720
That I drew.
ֵHere

211
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:50,400
You know, it looks a bit like the drawing...

212
00:11:50,560 --> 00:11:52,960
Exactly. So I was a genius too.

213
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:54,960
So why didn't she want to hang my drawings?

214
00:11:55,040 --> 00:11:57,720
Tell me, what are you, spaced out?
You know your mom asked me

215
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:59,000
if I hit the girls?

216
00:11:59,080 --> 00:12:00,280
ֵBeni

217
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:02,240
Come on, I want
to finish this and go home. Enough.

218
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:03,800
So yeah?
-Shh.

219
00:12:04,440 --> 00:12:07,720
I think they're listening...
-What?

220
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:10,480
Michal, you said you wanted to tell him something?

221
00:12:11,040 --> 00:12:13,400
Yeah, babe, come on, let's tell Adam later.

222
00:12:13,520 --> 00:12:16,600
What happened, babe?
-Yeah? Okay. Alright.

223
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:19,600
Wow, I can't believe it, I'm so excited.

224
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:21,400
So babe, you can. Come on, get to it, babe,

225
00:12:21,480 --> 00:12:22,400
get to it.
-Okay, okay, alright.

226
00:12:22,560 --> 00:12:24,800
I hope it's not another pair
of new shoes she bought

227
00:12:24,920 --> 00:12:25,800
because that would really annoy me.

228
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:29,240
Rivka, let the girl speak.
-Thanks, Pinchas.

229
00:12:29,600 --> 00:12:32,920
Okay, so like this. So as
you know, in recent years I've been...

230
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:35,760
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

231
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:37,520
Adam.

232
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:40,120
Meet Michal.

233
00:12:41,440 --> 00:12:45,000
You told me she’s divorced but no, I didn’t connect the dots.

234
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:48,960
No, at that moment my sukkah's covering flew away. I'm exposed

235
00:12:49,120 --> 00:12:52,120
and mostly dying.
-Babe, control yourself. Okay?

236
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:55,400
You didn't tell them, huh, B'la?
-Isn't it fun to surprise?

237
00:12:55,680 --> 00:12:58,680
Very much, I'm Michal.
-Yeah, we know,

238
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:01,240
Michal Amadoreski. Hello.

239
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:03,440
I hope I remember. I'm Pinchas, very nice.

240
00:13:03,680 --> 00:13:07,520
Is this a cooking show?
-Babe, Shai. His brother.

241
00:13:07,600 --> 00:13:10,880
Big problem.
-What... what... what's going on?

242
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:14,200
Yeah, hey, hey. Adam, what's up?

243
00:13:14,280 --> 00:13:17,440
I need to have a quick chat with you
in the kitchen, so if you could just...

244
00:13:17,960 --> 00:13:19,280
Sure, go ahead.
-Come on.

245
00:13:20,440 --> 00:13:23,360
Don't bother her too much.
-Why would we bother her?

246
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:25,240
What, are we animals? Come on, sit down.

247
00:13:25,320 --> 00:13:26,560
Thanks.
-Sit.

248
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:34,160
No, I'm dying. You're dating Adam?
-Michal, chill out.

249
00:13:34,280 --> 00:13:38,160
I read that you're dating the... the... son.

250
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:41,400
Pinchas, what's the kid's name?
-Is this a cooking show?

251
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:46,840
Hello, hello, hello. What’s this? What, are you a kid?

252
00:13:46,920 --> 00:13:48,960
What, are you a kid?
-What’s wrong with you?

253
00:13:49,040 --> 00:13:51,400
I'll tell you what I don't have.
I don't have a celeb dating us.

254
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:54,760
No. I don't have one. No celeb. No.
-What do you want?

255
00:13:54,840 --> 00:13:56,360
Spill it, share, report.

256
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:58,880
What? What?
-Where? How? Why?

257
00:13:58,960 --> 00:14:00,760
Give details, explain, give examples.

258
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:03,000
If there are pictures on the phone, it’ll be in the gallery.

259
00:14:03,640 --> 00:14:06,320
You guys are nuts.
-Of course we're nuts. We're in shock.

260
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:09,640
Spill it!
-We met at a party, talked, went out.

261
00:14:09,760 --> 00:14:11,120
No pictures.
-Liar!

262
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:13,440
I'm asking you, don’t embarrass me, okay?

263
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:15,160
Actually...

264
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:18,600
We wanted her.

265
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:22,960
With me it’s not a problem, but with Itamar...
you know him.

266
00:14:23,120 --> 00:14:25,360
What about Itamar? Sorry, I'm the one who dated a celeb.

267
00:14:25,520 --> 00:14:27,240
Yeah? The beauty queen of Ramat Gan is not a celeb.

268
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:28,840
In Ramat Gan, everyone knows her.

269
00:14:30,680 --> 00:14:31,880
True.

270
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:36,800
Your hair looks really nice like that.
-Thanks.

271
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:39,520
Wow, I can’t believe we’re
just sitting here like friends.

272
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:41,480
Friends...
-Don’t mind her,

273
00:14:41,560 --> 00:14:43,040
she doesn’t go out much.

274
00:14:43,120 --> 00:14:46,360
Girls, can we have a little quiet? I'm trying
to watch dancers prepare lamb.

275
00:14:46,840 --> 00:14:50,400
Pinchas, we have a guest here. Turn off
the TV. It’s rude.

276
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:53,920
Okay, done.
-It’s fine, you can leave it on.

277
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:56,680
I like this show too.
-So what...

278
00:14:57,480 --> 00:15:01,680
Does Adam treat you well?
-Adam treats me really well.

279
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:04,440
Great. What do you do?
-Oh, Pinchas...

280
00:15:04,560 --> 00:15:07,320
No, it’s fine.
-I’m trying to be polite to the guest. You asked.

281
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:10,000
You know, I’m involved in all sorts of things.

282
00:15:10,080 --> 00:15:13,320
Yeah. But what? What? You wake up in the morning, what do you do?

283
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:16,040
Where are you going?
-I wake up in the morning and then...

284
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:19,840
Either I have meetings or shoots...
-Shoots. X-ray technician. Got it.

285
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:22,680
At "Maccabi" or "Clalit"?
-I’m at "Maccabi" and it’s really not related.

286
00:15:22,760 --> 00:15:24,920
Good, nice, good job. Can we go back to the lamb?

287
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:27,120
Pinchas!
-No, I’m totally dying.

288
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:29,960
Don’t mind him, he’s a simple guy.
He’s from the village.

289
00:15:31,880 --> 00:15:33,680
Do you think we can calm Mom down?

290
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:36,600
You made me laugh. Mom's in full-on panic mode.

291
00:15:36,680 --> 00:15:38,880
Yeah, huh?
-Come on.

292
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:42,320
We're coming. Adam, Adam, check out this drawing for a sec.

293
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:43,800
What do you think?
-What is it?

294
00:15:44,160 --> 00:15:45,920
This is Shai's little one who drew it.

295
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:49,840
The parents are stressed.
-Who’s that in the drawing? Is that Shavi?

296
00:15:49,960 --> 00:15:53,120
I think so.
-The drawing is a bit scary.

297
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:54,640
A bit scary?
-Isn’t it?

298
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:56,520
The first time I saw it, I almost peed myself.

299
00:15:56,600 --> 00:15:59,720
Because her hands are a bit scary, they’re like...
-Scary!

300
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:06,320
Edmika, your friend is lovely.

301
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:08,080
Just lovely.
-Right?

302
00:16:08,640 --> 00:16:10,360
A celebrity, huh, Mom?
-Oh, Itamar,

303
00:16:10,440 --> 00:16:12,760
I'm not that superficial. I can tell the difference.

304
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:15,080
She's just a wonderful person. Classy.

305
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:18,160
Not for you, but classy.
-Thanks, Mom.

306
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:20,960
Itamar, you finished all the schnitzels.

307
00:16:21,520 --> 00:16:24,600
Everyone ate them.
-Get out of my kitchen. Both of you. Now.

308
00:16:30,520 --> 00:16:32,760
Dad, the TV is perfectly fine.
I don't get what the problem is.

309
00:16:32,920 --> 00:16:34,800
No, you know how Mom is with her nonsense.

310
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:37,160
It's not sharp enough, so she wants to replace the TV.

311
00:16:37,640 --> 00:16:39,360
Speaking of sharp, how's Shabi?

312
00:16:40,960 --> 00:16:44,960
No, I didn't get the connection
but Shabi's doing great. Why?

313
00:16:45,040 --> 00:16:48,560
Just curious. After all, she's the bride,
I want to know if everything's okay

314
00:16:48,640 --> 00:16:52,400
with her, with you guys. I mean,
if you're not fighting, say.

315
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:54,240
She's not taking it out on the girls, right?

316
00:16:54,320 --> 00:16:56,560
Dad, only Stanley Fischer is "say." Got it?

317
00:16:56,720 --> 00:16:59,000
Everything's fine with her, everything's fine
with me, and everything's fine with the girls.

318
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:02,120
What's up with you, Bgid?
-No, it's just Mom with her quirks.

319
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:05,160
So that's why you brought me here?
Amdursky's sitting in the living room,

320
00:17:05,319 --> 00:17:08,359
and I'm here on a wild goose chase?
-That girl from Ramat Gan, is her name Amdursky?

321
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:10,960
I've already forgotten.
-Funny.

322
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:17,800
Wow, if I had known you were coming,
I would have put in a bit more effort with my clothes.

323
00:17:17,960 --> 00:17:20,640
You look lovely.
-What, this? I just threw something on.

324
00:17:21,119 --> 00:17:22,960
Michali, can you tilt
your head a bit to the right?

325
00:17:23,119 --> 00:17:25,200
You're blocking my view of the guest.
-Mom, enough.

326
00:17:25,280 --> 00:17:27,800
Your new hair is stunning.
-Thanks.

327
00:17:27,880 --> 00:17:30,120
What hair? In the health fund magazine?

328
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:32,720
No, Pinchas, the hair with the little swimsuit.

329
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:35,320
Why would an X-ray technician pose in a tiny swimsuit?

330
00:17:35,800 --> 00:17:38,680
I'm not an X-ray technician.
-Oh, are you in the internship stage?

331
00:17:39,080 --> 00:17:40,800
Pinchas, you don't know what you're talking about?

332
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:43,520
Of course I know who I'm...
I'm not senile yet.

333
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:46,560
With Adam's girlfriend.
-It's fine, Pinchas. Nothing happened.

334
00:17:50,080 --> 00:17:51,720
Where's the bathroom?

335
00:17:55,720 --> 00:17:57,040
At the end of the hallway. Everything okay?

336
00:17:57,920 --> 00:18:01,600
Of course it's okay. You know,
I need to use the bathroom sometimes too.

337
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:07,320
Run before it gets away from you.
-Shai. His brother.

338
00:18:07,480 --> 00:18:08,880
I don't remember if...
-Shai.

339
00:18:09,640 --> 00:18:11,480
Tell me, Pinchas, you really don't know her?

340
00:18:11,560 --> 00:18:13,040
I didn't get it. Is she famous?

341
00:18:13,120 --> 00:18:16,640
Pinchas, sometimes I ask myself:
Where did you find her?

342
00:18:16,720 --> 00:18:20,440
Dad, it's fine. Guys,
she's a person. Just like us.

343
00:18:20,560 --> 00:18:23,680
Just that she looks better,
much, much better.

344
00:18:23,760 --> 00:18:27,240
You remember I'm sitting here, right?
-Yeah, honey, you look good too.

345
00:18:27,560 --> 00:18:30,000
Hey, Michali, we're all here now.
You said you wanted to share something.

346
00:18:30,360 --> 00:18:33,520
Oh, right. Okay, okay, okay.

347
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,880
What do you mean "famous"? What is she famous for?

348
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:39,080
Don't you see Michali
wants to tell us something exciting?

349
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:42,120
Oh, right. Sorry. Go ahead.
-So, like this, in recent years...

350
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:45,400
Do you think she's managing in the bathroom?
-I think she's managing.

351
00:18:45,480 --> 00:18:47,960
No, really. Maybe we should check.
-Okay, can I? Just a sec.

352
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:50,840
Yes, yes—
-Okay, so like this, in recent years,

353
00:18:51,040 --> 00:18:53,800
as you know...
-There you are, back. How was it?

354
00:18:54,440 --> 00:18:58,640
Routine. Your home is lovely.
-Thanks.

355
00:18:58,760 --> 00:19:02,280
Really, I keep telling
Pinchas we need to renovate

356
00:19:02,440 --> 00:19:04,360
but he doesn't want to, he says it's not necessary.

357
00:19:04,480 --> 00:19:06,800
Come on, come on, I'll show you the kitchen.

358
00:19:08,520 --> 00:19:09,960
Give her a schnitzel.
-Okay.

359
00:19:10,360 --> 00:19:11,720
You haven't had one like this.
-Mom...

360
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:15,840
Sit down, come to my parents' room for a sec.
I want to show you something.

361
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:18,000
I changed the sheets.
_Refreshing

362
00:19:18,080 --> 00:19:19,920
Just in case you wanted to know.

363
00:19:20,520 --> 00:19:23,840
So what’s she famous for?
Did she invent something? Did she win an award?

364
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:27,960
Is she an actress? A dancer? A host?
-All of the above, Pinchas.

365
00:19:28,160 --> 00:19:30,320
You're really embarrassing me. Seriously.

366
00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:33,920
After that, you wonder why I
don’t want to go out with you anywhere.

367
00:19:35,080 --> 00:19:36,600
What’s going on?
-That’s what I’m asking you.

368
00:19:36,680 --> 00:19:38,720
What am I missing here?
-I don’t know.

369
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:41,200
In your family, nothing
can surprise me anymore.

370
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:44,320
Except for Adam’s new girlfriend. She’s pretty healthy, huh?

371
00:19:44,400 --> 00:19:45,560
Totally.
-Shai, be careful.

372
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:47,440
You said it.
-I’m allowed.

373
00:19:50,160 --> 00:19:52,600
How sweet.
-I apologize for the...

374
00:19:55,320 --> 00:19:58,320
I apologize for my family.
-Come on, Adam, don’t be stupid.

375
00:19:58,720 --> 00:20:01,240
Besides, the warnings about your mom
were totally exaggerated.

376
00:20:01,360 --> 00:20:03,080
No, really. She seems like a really nice woman.

377
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:07,640
Ah, I’m glad. Cool.

378
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:10,840
What’s this painting?
-Oh, sorry.

379
00:20:10,920 --> 00:20:13,160
I hope I’m not interrupting.
-No, not at all.

380
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:18,680
Say, whose painting is that on the fridge?

381
00:20:18,760 --> 00:20:21,000
It’s Shai’s daughter’s.
-Oh.

382
00:20:21,080 --> 00:20:22,760
Are you telling me?

383
00:20:24,920 --> 00:20:26,120
Here you are.
-Oh my.

384
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:27,520
Shai. Shai.

385
00:20:29,920 --> 00:20:30,920
Sh.

386
00:20:34,720 --> 00:20:36,720
Okay, is everyone here?
-Yeah.

387
00:20:36,840 --> 00:20:39,560
So can I finally announce?
-Go, baby, go.

388
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:45,520
Okay, so after three weeks, I finally
finished the art therapy course.

389
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:46,840
Wow.
-Wow.

390
00:20:46,920 --> 00:20:48,400
That’s really wonderful news.
-Thanks.

391
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:53,360
So what, Michal, are you studying something?
-Actually, no one knows about it.

392
00:20:53,440 --> 00:20:55,360
But I have a bachelor’s degree in psychology.

393
00:20:55,440 --> 00:20:57,440
D.
-Wow, wow.

394
00:20:57,520 --> 00:21:00,440
Speaking of psychology, can I
talk about the painting on the fridge for a sec?

395
00:21:00,520 --> 00:21:03,920
Of course. Nice, huh?
-Look, there’s a problem here.

396
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:08,720
The painting is cloudy and dark. The kids are small and crying.

397
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:13,400
The dominant figure is dark and big
with long nails and sharp teeth.

398
00:21:13,560 --> 00:21:17,040
I’d say the mom in the painting

399
00:21:17,160 --> 00:21:20,000
is kind of... a monster.

400
00:21:22,080 --> 00:21:23,840
I’m not saying that.

401
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:28,840
That’s what someone with a
bachelor’s degree in psychology says.

402
00:21:29,880 --> 00:21:32,680
My sweet girl, who’s in the painting?

403
00:21:33,080 --> 00:21:34,160
Grandma Raanan.

404
00:21:39,760 --> 00:21:41,400
It’s not that you don’t paint well, sweetie,

405
00:21:41,560 --> 00:21:44,560
it’s just that Grandma doesn’t like
to hang the painting on the fridge

406
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:48,800
because she thinks the fridge
looks better without it.

407
00:21:48,960 --> 00:21:50,920
It’s called “fridge design.”
What does she call it?

408
00:21:51,040 --> 00:21:53,120
Fridge aesthetics.
-The aesthetics of the fridge.

409
00:21:53,200 --> 00:21:54,320
You’ll understand that when you grow up.

410
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:57,160
Yeah, you paint just like
Dad did when he was your age.

411
00:21:57,240 --> 00:21:58,640
Of course. Because you had the same model.

412
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:02,240
It also doesn’t leave room. I’m speaking from experience.

413
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:04,440
You can live with it, honey.

414
00:22:08,080 --> 00:22:09,240
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom, Pinchas.

415
00:22:09,320 --> 00:22:10,160
Shabbat Shalom, Riki.

416
00:22:11,280 --> 00:22:14,880
I’m not Riki.
-Isn’t that Riki?

417
00:22:16,320 --> 00:22:21,160
Painting. The daughter...
-The daughter... the girl painted at kindergarten

418
00:22:21,280 --> 00:22:24,320
and we thought she... that it...
-No, she painted this in the car just now.

419
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:26,320
Right, why am I changing the setup?

420
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:28,480
So what, Michal
-Amidorsky.

421
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:30,440
Are you learning something?

422
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:34,880
Your mom hung the trip on the fridge... the trip.

423
00:22:35,160 --> 00:22:38,880
Your mom hung the drawing on the fridge... sorry.

424
00:22:38,960 --> 00:22:41,200
Schnitzels?
!Shai
-Oh no.

425
00:22:42,240 --> 00:22:43,720
None?
-No.

426
00:22:44,120 --> 00:22:47,600
Okay
let's take a break
there's nothing.

427
00:22:49,840 --> 00:22:52,040
Fine, I just wanted to say.
-You confused her.

428
00:22:53,760 --> 00:22:55,240
Hey, are there schnitzels?

